title: shakeup especially
extract: Definition of shake up (Entry 2 of 2) transitive verb. 1 obsolete : chide, scold. 2 : to jar by or as if by a physical shock the collision shook up both drivers. 3 : to effect an extensive and often drastic reorganization of.
